snippet.textDisplay:
"... a smaller GPU is theoretically easier to cool"
?? I doubt it... I'm glad you said "theoretically" because I doubt that's true. Assuming there's less transistors (we still don't know everything about the APU and adjacent chips) then the HIGHER CLOCK FREQUENCY of the PS5 GPU means it will consume more power per transistor. So using TFLOPS only as a metric which may be roughly comparable given similar architectures then we're looking at a 17% difference. So the power draw (ignoring CPU and other things) might be within 5 to 10% of each other... and considering the DESIGN OF THE CASE probably isn't as efficient for cooling it's probably HARDER TO COOL than the new XBOX.
